stories.story_text:
I recently tried applying to accelerators on AngelList and received an acceptance letter to an accelerator called 'OneTraction', without talking to anyone or nothing, my team was asked to pay an "acceptance" fee of 390$, this startup boasts on their mentors page Sean Parker as a founder and an investor and Reid Hoffman as a mentor, after some research, I was unable to find any press about "OneTraction" which is odd considering the names mentoring this accelerator

This led me to believe that the accelerator in question is a scam which tries to rob us poor entrepreneurs from our food money in a critical time.\nIf I'm mistaken, I'm sorry, I would love to be mistaken, does anyone know of this?

Profile in question: https://angel.co/onetraction/
